<h1>SMTPt</h1>
<p>File: <a href='https://github.com/nathan242/sysadmin-tools/blob/master/SMTPt.py'>LINK</a></p>

<h4>Introduction</h4>
<p>Simple SMTP server testing script.</p>
<p>You can use this to send an email via a specified SMTP server. All data sent and received will be output to the console. Useful for testing if an SMTP server is set up correctly.</p>

<div class='code'>
<pre>
=== SMTP Tester ===
Usage:
./SMTPt.py [SMTP_SERVER] [FROM] [TO] [SUBJECT] [BODY]
./SMTPt.py [SMTP_SERVER] [FROM] [TO] - < [DATA]
</pre>
</div>

<p>Example:</p>
<div class='code'>
<pre>
./SMTPt.py smtp.example.org "&lt;sender@example.org&gt;" "&lt;recipient@example.org&gt;" "Test email" "Hello World!"
</pre>
</div>

<p>Instead of [SUBJECT] and [BODY], you can specify "-" to use data from STDIN as message data.</p>

